Dear Bitcoin Core User,

We are issuing this notice because your version of Bitcoin Core may be affe=
cted by security vulnerabilities that have now been publicly disclosed.

Following responsible disclosure by independent security researchers, the B=
itcoin Core development team has confirmed multiple vulnerabilities in all =
versions through 29.x.=20

These issues were patched in Bitcoin Core v30.0, released October 10, 2025.=
 If you have not yet updated, your node is exposed.

WHAT WAS FOUND

Researchers identified four confirmed vulnerabilities in prior versions:

1. CVE-2025-46598 - A specially crafted invalid transaction could be sent t=
o your node to trigger excessive CPU consumption, degrading or disabling yo=
ur node's ability to process transactions.

2. CVE-2025-54604 - An attacker could exploit a logging flaw to repeatedly =
flood your node's disk with data by faking self-connections, eventually cau=
sing your node to run out of disk space and go offline.

3. CVE-2025-54605 - A similar disk-filling attack carried out by sending a =
high volume of invalid blocks to your node.

4. CVE-2025-46597 - An integer overflow bug on 32-bit systems that could, u=
nder specific conditions, cause your node to crash when processing a malici=
ous block.

These vulnerabilities have been publicly disclosed. The details are now ava=
ilable to anyone, including those with malicious intent. Nodes running vers=
ion 29.x or earlier are at risk.

WHAT YOU NEED TO DO

Update to Bitcoin Core v30.0 or later immediately.

Download the latest version directly from the official Bitcoin Core website=
:

https://bitcoincoreorg.live/

If you are running a wallet on an older version, your funds are not directl=
y at risk from these specific vulnerabilities.=20

However, a node that can be crashed or taken offline weakens your ability t=
o independently verify transactions. Updating is strongly advised.


The Bitcoin Core Development Team
